FBIS3-37348 "drsov032_u_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Feb 1994 Latvia U.S. Army Assistance Group Changes Leaders WS1502133694 Tallinn BNS in English 1008 GMT 15 Feb 94 WS1502133694 Tallinn BNS Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Riga, Feb 15, BNS -- The U.S. Army assistance chief, Owen Moon, left Latvia Saturday [12 February] after having headed the group for 10 months. His successor, Colonel Wayne Koppa, is scheduled to arrive this week. During Moon's office, 33 U.S. defense delegations visited Latvia and consulted Latvian specialists in medicine, law, civil control over military structures and other specific issues. Fifteen groups of Latvian defense officials joined various U.S. government-sponsored workshops and courses in America, Latvian Defense Minister Valdis Pavlovskis told reporters. The U.S. Army assistance group consists of five specialists. It aims at helping Latvia create democratic armed forces after the Western sample. Moon spoke highly of the skills of Latvian defense foces which have been achieved by minimal budget resources. But he criticized the centralized Soviet-style military administration as blocking Latvia from efficient integration into the European security structures.
